               <history>
                  <provenance><persName key="person_101089289" role="fmo">John Hall, physician, of Maidstone, 1529/30–1568/9</persName> (see DNB): The name of 'John Halle' appears twice: <q type="price">precium xxiiij<hi rend="superscript">s</hi></q>: also on fol. ij <persName key="person_3292" role="sgn">'John Capon' (or Caxton)</persName>.</provenance>
                  <acquisition when="1612"> This appears to be the 'Book of Surgerie in English' presented by <persName key="person_15121578" role="dnr">Thomas Twyne</persName> in 1612, but not referenced till about 1620–25.</acquisition>
               </history>
